==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[captare]]''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪs|-eɪs]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#<!--NAction-->The action of the verb "to chase".
#<!--NHunt-->A [[hunt]].
#<!--NProperty--> {{UK}} A large [[country]] [[estate]] where [[game]] may be [[shoot|shot]] or [[hunt]]ed.
# Anything being chased, especially a vessel in time of war
#{{nautical}} Any of the [[gun]]s that fire directly ahead or astern; either a [[bow chase]] or [[stern chase]]

